          "type": "text",
          "text": " is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server. Scalar functions return a single value and are used to encapsulate reusable logic that can be applied to individual rows in a query. This function is designed to determine whether a contact exists in a database, based on specific criteria provided through input parameters."
